Template Builder box effect width mode:
- Time: 2026-05-10 KST.
- Decision:
  - Box effect width mode belongs to the ratio-common text effect style, not to ratio-local position/size.
  - `sizing: 'text'` keeps the existing text-fit behavior and uses `paddingX` as text-side padding.
  - `sizing: 'fixed'` hides `paddingX`, uses `box.width`, and lets horizontal preview resize update the common box width instead of the ratio-local text layer width.
  - Text-fit box mode exposes only vertical resize handles in preview so users cannot stretch the box width from the canvas.
  - Python text artifact rendering now consumes the same `sizing/width/paddingX` contract so preview artifacts and sample/final render overlays do not drift.
