Template Builder text-fit box center/move anchor fix:
- Time: 2026-05-10 KST.
- Root cause:
  - Text-fit box preview artifacts can have a visible frame x that differs from the persisted layer `x` because center/right text alignment adds an artifact offset inside the layer width.
  - Canvas move and the `가로 중앙` action were storing the visible artifact frame x directly as `layer.x`, so the next artifact render drifted horizontally.
- Decision:
  - Keep using the visible artifact frame for selection, measurement, and centering calculations.
  - Convert visible frame x back to the persisted layer anchor x when emitting ratio-local x patches.
  - Apply the conversion to both canvas drag patches and the stage toolbar horizontal-center action.
